         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>85f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I honor you leading the caravan unsurpassed ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>130</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>161</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>447</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>161</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>469</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>119</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>87</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// (18) your soul is pervaded by emptiness; you have rejected every merit and sin ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>161</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>283</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>65</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the somnifacient for the brahmins, named [wrong] imagination, has been cut off ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3 #b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>210f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(Abgeschnitten worden) [ist] das Schlafmittel der (Bra)hmanen namens [falsche] Vorstellung. Eben dadurch [ist] von dir zerspalten worden (jegliche) Hinderung des Verstandes. ... in allem [bzw. in allen ... ] wirst du nicht gehemmt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The sleeping draught of the (bra)hmins called [false] notion [has] (been cut off). Exactly therefore, (any) hindrance of the mind [has] been cloven apart by you ... in all [or: in all ...] you are not hindered.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>210-1</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>296</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>96</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">Mātṛceṭa's Varṇāhavarṇa II.</note><note type="philcomment">For the correspondence with Skt. see <bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1987"/></bibl>:</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment"><hi>ñare</hi>: The meaning here seems to be 'sin, bad deed' rather than the usual 'hell'. Cf. VAV2.37 <hi>prahīṇapuṇyapāpāya</hi> "Dem, der Vergehen und Verdienst aufgegeben hat" (Hartmann JU 1987: xx).</note></p>
         </div>
